{
  "text": "The immunoreactive angiotensin II present in the cerebrospinal fluid is of extrarenal origin, as it is present in bilaterally nephrectomized animals and [ 3 H] angiotensin has been shown not to penetrate the bloodcerebrospinal fluid barrier [CITATION_1] . As there are no detectable activities of renin-like enzymes [CITATION_2] or, as shown in the Results section, of angiotensinases in canine cerebrospinal fluid, it is unlikely that Des-Asp'-angiotensin II is formed in cerebrospinal fluid.",
  "correct_citation": {
